  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Due to the lack of an execution environment, LLMs struggle to accurately derive expected outputs for complex inputs [84], making assertion errors the primary cause of test failures (accounting for over 85% [84,161]).",
    "Systemic evaluations also confirm that the ability of LLMs to generate correct assertions significantly degrades, particularly in scenarios involving arithmetic calculations and loop iterations [21].",
    "In certain complex scenarios, LLMs may fail completely to produce any correct assertions; for instance, a 0% success rate was observed when testing a CRC_GEN functional block [80].",
    "This reflects the inherent limitations of LLMs as probabilistic models in tasks requiring precise logical reasoning and numerical computation.",
    "To address this core challenge, researchers have explored several avenues."
